METAR Nhill Airport - YNHL

Nhill Airport is a small airport in Victoria, Australia. The airport is located at latitude -36.31096 and longitude 141.64515. The airport has 2 runways: 9/27 and 18/36. The ICAO airport code of this field is YNHL. The airport is in the Melbourne FIR.

This aviation weather observation was made for Avalon Airport on August 30, 2024 21:00, local time.

Airport observations

The wind is from direction 320° with a speed of 16 kt.

Visibility is 10 km or more.

There are nil cloud detected. No ceiling has been observed.

The temperature and wind chill are 13 °C. The dew point is 5 °C, the relative humidity is 59%. The air pressure at sea level is 997 hPa (QNH).

Daylight period

Today the sun rises at 06:56 and sets at 18:11. This applies to Nhill Airport, the universal daylight period may be different. The difference between the local time and UTC is +10 hour. Daylight saving time is currently in progress.
